      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">8.405-5</ph> Small business.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d461e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d476e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  Although the preference programs of part <xref href="FAR-i1101928.dita#i1101928"
                        base="i1101928"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19</xref> are not mandatory in this subpart, in accordance with section 1331 of Public Law 111-240 (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C. 644</xref>(r))-</p>
               <ol id="d461e29" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d476e22" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        Ordering activity contracting officers may, at their discretion-</p>
                     <ol id="d461e39" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d476e28" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              Set aside orders for any of the small business concerns identified in <xref href="FAR-i1101771.dita#i1101771"
                                    base="i1101771"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">19.000</xref>(a)(3); and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d476e36" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              Set aside BPAs for any of the small business concerns identified in <xref href="FAR-i1101771.dita#i1101771"
                                    base="i1101771"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">19.000</xref>(a)(3).</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d476e44" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        When setting aside orders and BPAs-</p>
                     <ol id="d461e75" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d476e50" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              Follow the ordering procedures for Federal Supply Schedules at <xref href="FAR-i1117534.dita#i1117534"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">8.405-1</xref>, <xref href="FAR-i1117591.dita#i1117591"
                                    base="i1117591"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">8.405-2</xref>, and <xref href="FAR-i1117655.dita#i1117655"
                                    base="i1117655"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">8.405-3</xref>; and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d476e64" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              The specific small business program eligibility requirements identified in part <xref href="FAR-i1101928.dita#i1101928"
                                    base="i1101928"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">19</xref> apply.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d476e72" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  Orders placed under schedule contracts may be credited toward the ordering activityâ€™s small business goals. For purposes of reporting an order placed with a small business schedule contractor, an ordering agency may only take credit if the awardee meets a size standard that corresponds to the North American Industry Classification System code assigned to the order in accordance with <xref href="FAR-i1101844.dita#i1101844"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.102</xref>(b)(3). Ordering activities should rely on the small business representations made by schedule contractors at the contract level (but see section <xref href="FAR-i19_301-2.dita#i19_301-2"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.301-2</xref>(b)(2) concerning rerepresentation for an order).
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d476e83" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  Ordering activities may consider socio-economic status when identifying contractor(s) for consideration or competition for award of an order or BPA. At a minimum, ordering activities should consider, if available, at least one small business, veteran-owned small business, service disabled veteran-owned small business, HUBZone small business, women-owned small business, or small disadvantaged business schedule contractor(s). GSA Advantage! and Schedules e-Library at <xref href="http://www.gsa.gov/fas"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">http://www.gsa.gov/fas</xref> contain information on the small business representations of Schedule contractors.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d476e91" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  For orders exceeding the micro-purchase threshold, ordering activities should give preference to the items of small business concerns when two or more items at the same delivered price will satisfy the requirement.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
